The paper deals with the problem of vertex coloring in a graph in the semi-streaming model, which is a subfield of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the offline setting, which involves simple greedy algorithms, and the arboricity of a graph, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The algorithms presented in the paper are randomized, which is a common technique in algorithm design and analysis (cs.AL). The paper also mentions the maximum degree and bounded arboricity of a graph, which are topics in computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT), respectively.
